# .mailmap — canonical author identity map
#
# Prevents leaderboard splitting when contributors commit under multiple
# email addresses (work laptop vs personal, old vs new address, etc).
#
# Format:
#   Canonical Name <canonical@email.com> <alias@email.com>
#   Canonical Name <canonical@email.com> Old Name <alias@email.com>
#
# Examples (uncomment and fill in real entries):
#
# Jane Smith <jane@company.com> <jane.smith@gmail.com>
# Jane Smith <jane@company.com> J. Smith <jsmith@oldcompany.com>
# Bob Jones <bob@company.com> Robert Jones <robert@company.com>
#
# Verify the map is working:
#   git log --format='%aN <%aE>' | sort -u
